{"_path":"/blog/en/tips_of_vim","_dir":"en","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","_empty":false,"title":"Tips of Vim","description":"Vim is my preferred text editor, and I have installed the vim plugin in every IDE on my computer. With my extensive experience in using vim, I would like to share some useful tips with you.","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h1","props":{"id":"tips-of-vim"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tips of Vim"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Vim is my preferred text editor, and I have installed the vim plugin in every IDE on my computer. With my extensive experience in using vim, I would like to share some useful tips with you."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"copy-contents-into-system-clipboard"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Copy contents into system clipboard"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Unlike conventional text editors, Vim uses a unique feature called \"register\" to store copied content. By default, when you use the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"y"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (yank) or "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"p"}]},{"type":"text","value":" (paste) commands, Vim utilizes the default register. This can cause issues when trying to paste text from inside Vim to outside applications or when attempting to copy text in the opposite direction. To overcome this limitation, you can utilize the "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"+"}]},{"type":"text","value":" register. Simply prefix your "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"p"}]},{"type":"text","value":" or "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"y"}]},{"type":"text","value":" commands with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\""}]},{"type":"text","value":" followed by "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"+"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to interact directly with the system clipboard."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"paste-text-in-command-line-mode"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Paste text in command-line mode"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Typing the word you want to search or replace by hand in search/command mode can be quite annoying. Luckily, Vim provides a way to directly paste word in the command-line. First, copy the content you want to search/replace into a Vim register (use "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"+"}]},{"type":"text","value":" register if the content to copy is from outside Vim). Then, type "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ctrl + R + register-name"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to paste the content in that register into Vim command line."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you simply want to paste a word under your cursor, try "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ctrl + R + Ctrl + W"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"interactive-string-substitution"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Interactive string substitution"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Vim enables global string substitution, but occasionally, unintended strings are replaced. For example, if you intend to replace the word "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"bar"}]},{"type":"text","value":" with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"foo"}]},{"type":"text","value":" globally, a word like "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"barbie"}]},{"type":"text","value":" would inadvertently change to "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"foobie"}]},{"type":"text","value":". To avoid this, you can append a "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"c"}]},{"type":"text","value":" to the command."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"For example, to interactively replace "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"bar"}]},{"type":"text","value":" with "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"foo"}]},{"type":"text","value":", you can use the command "},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":":%s/bar/foo/gc"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"substitute-texts-within-visual-selection"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"substitute texts within visual selection"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"To substitute text within a visual selection, use following command after selecting the desired text:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"className":["language-undefined"],"code":":'<,'>s/\\%Vpattern/replacement/g\n"},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"pre","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code","props":{"__ignoreMap":""},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{"class":"line","line":1},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"span","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":":'<,'>s/\\%Vpattern/replacement/g"}]}]}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Explanation of components:"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":":'<,'>"}]},{"type":"text","value":":  is automatically generated upon entering command mode ("},{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":":"}]},{"type":"text","value":") after making a visual selection."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"code-inline","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"%V"}]},{"type":"text","value":": This modifier limits the substitution operation to the text that has been visually selected."}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[{"id":"copy-contents-into-system-clipboard","depth":2,"text":"Copy contents into system clipboard"},{"id":"paste-text-in-command-line-mode","depth":2,"text":"Paste text in command-line mode"},{"id":"interactive-string-substitution","depth":2,"text":"Interactive string substitution"},{"id":"substitute-texts-within-visual-selection","depth":2,"text":"substitute texts within visual selection"}]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:en:51.tips_of_vim.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/en/51.tips_of_vim.md","_extension":"md"}